@page "/how-it-works"
<h1>How It Works</h1>
<section class="steps">
    <div class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <h3>Browse Open Tasks</h3>
        <p>Clients post development tasks with bounties. Browse by complexity, language, or reward amount.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <h3>Submit a Pull Request</h3>
        <p>Write your code and submit a public pull request. Multiple developers can submit PRs for the same task.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <h3>Complexity Scoring</h3>
        <p>Your PR is automatically scored based on files changed, lines added, language difficulty, and test coverage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <h3>Client Reviews and Approves</h3>
        <p>The client reviews all submitted PRs and chooses the best one to approve. On approval, the client is automatically charged the bounty amount.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <h3>Get Paid and Level Up</h3>
        <p>The developer receives payment via their preferred payout method. Earn XP, unlock badges, and climb the leaderboard with every approved PR.</p>
    </div>
</section>
